modStarterQuestWelcome:
{#--color-brown:If you're new to Wayward, this {/Starter Quest/} can help you survive by teaching you the basics. This optional walkthrough will take approximately 20-40 minutes.}

Press {BINDINGS:DialogQuests} to toggle this dialog.

Click "{/Complete Quest/}" to start the quest line.

modStarterQuestGearUp:
{#--color-brown:Attacking creatures will use items in your inventory when equipped to your main hand. Let's equip an item now.}

1. Open your equipment {(HELP/INTERFACE):dialog} with {BINDINGS:DialogEquipment} or click the equipment icon at the top of the screen.

2. Equip a tool or weapon by dragging it from your inventory to the equipment slot of your choice.

Alternatively, you can {BINDINGS:GameItemEquipToggle} to toggle it equipped or not.

{(HELP/HELD_ITEMS):Learn more about Held Items}

modStarterQuestActionSlots:
{#--color-brown:While facing most objects in the world, actions can be done via the action menu (performed with {BINDINGS:GameActions}) or the item action menu (performed with {BINDINGS:GameActionsItems}). Performing actions in this way can be tedious.}

Instead, you can add actions to your action bar so they can be performed with a single binding.

To add an action to an action slot simply hover over an action slot and use {BINDINGS:GameActionBarConfigure}. Choose "Chop" from the action menu that comes up and click "Done".

Now you can use the binding that is shown under the action slot. For example, the first slot uses {BINDINGS:GameActionBarUseSlot0}.

{#--color-brown:Using actions in this way will always pick the "best" item for the action from your inventory. Other common actions include "Mine", "Butcher", and "Start Fire" which can be set to different slots for ease of use.}

modStarterQuestItemActionSlots:
{#--color-brown:All items have a list of actions that can be performed with them at any time.}

{BINDINGS:GameItemMenu} to open an item's action menu.

{#--color-brown:Using actions in this way can be cumbersome. You can also use the action bar for items!}

- Drag and drop an item into an action slot.

- OR use one of the "Assign Action" bindings. While hovering over an item, use {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot0}, {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot1}, or {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot2} for example to use slot 1/2/3.

{#--color-brown:By default, this is a sequence bind, meaning you have to press one key, then the other instead of all at the same time.}
